The**Find Records Action**allows you to search for records within a specific module based on certain criteria and use those records within the flow.Topics Covered:

[How to Configure Find Records Action](https://support.salesmate.io/hc/en-us/articles/38138036610201-Find-Records#h_01J8PC0905MSSB1GP77KG8BSRF)[Practical Example](https://support.salesmate.io/hc/en-us/articles/38138036610201-Find-Records#h_01J8PDZ9AZR8FF6TDNHJC726RT)

### How to Configure Find Records Action

While setting up a Smart Flow, select**Find Records**Action.

![mceclip0.png](./images/mceclip0-9.png)

Once you select the**Find Records Action**, you will need to configure the following details:**Name**: Assign a concise and descriptive title for the action to clearly indicate its function.**Description**: Provide a brief overview of the action's purpose, explaining its role within the workflow.**Effective Module**: Identify the specific module from which you wish to retrieve records.**Filter Deal Records Using Given Conditions**: Establish the criteria that will be used to filter the records, ensuring you capture only the relevant entries based on your needs.**Sorting**: Specify the preferred method for organizing the retrieved records.Once the configuration is completed, hit**Save**.

![mceclip0(1).png](./images/mceclip01-4.png)

### Practical Example

When a contact is deleted, our automation flow will trigger to ensure a clean database. It will first search for all activities linked to the deleted contact and then remove those activities automatically. This helps maintain organization and prevents clutter in your records.
